`list` is iterable. If an object is iterable, we can call `.__iter__()` to get an iterator.

`[1, 2, 3].__iter__()` is an iterator.

Note: both iterable object and iterator object can be used in for loop:

    for i in [1, 2, 3]: print(i, end=' ')
    for i in [1, 2, 3].__iter__(): print(i, end=' ')
